# ── Rust build artifacts ───────────────────────────────────────────────
/target
**/target/
**/*.rs.bk

# Cargo.lock IS committed for binary crates (we want reproducible builds).
# Only the .bak file from cargo's recovery flow is ignored.
Cargo.lock.bak

# Incremental compilation cache.
**/*.incremental/

# Profile-guided optimisation files.
*.profraw
*.profdata

# ── OS / Editor cruft ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
desktop.ini
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.#*
\#*#

# IDE / editor config (per-user, not project-shared).
.idea/
.vscode/
*.code-workspace
.fleet/
.zed/

# ── Local app data ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Quay's runtime data lives outside the repo (under
# `~/.local/share/quay/` on Linux, `~/Library/Application Support/quay/`
# on macOS, `%APPDATA%\quay\` on Windows). If something accidentally
# writes to the repo root, ignore the common names so they don't get
# committed.
quay.db
quay.db-*
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-journal
*.sqlite-shm
*.sqlite-wal
quay.log
*.log

# Worktrees that get created in-place during testing should never be
# tracked. The convention is `<repo>/.worktrees/<slug>` (Polish 1).
/.worktrees/

# ── Build outputs ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.dSYM/
*.pdb
*.exe
*.dll
*.so
*.dylib

# ── Test scratch ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.tmp
*.bak
*.orig
*.rej

# ── Tarballs / archives accidentally generated locally ─────────────────
*.tar
*.tar.gz
*.zip
*.7z

# ── Coverage + flamegraph reports ──────────────────────────────────────
tarpaulin-report.html
cobertura.xml
flamegraph.svg
perf.data
perf.data.old

# ── Skia / Slint build cache (if regenerated next to the source) ───────
skia-build/
slint-build-cache/

# ── Personal scratch ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Anything starting with `.scratch-` or `_scratch_` is treated as local
# experimentation and should never be committed.
.scratch-*
_scratch_*
SCRATCH.md
TODO.local.md
NOTES.local.md
